Terraform supported syntaxes
============================
1- Single‑Line Comment (#)
      # This is a single-line comment
   Single‑Line Comment (//)
      // This is also a single-line comment
   Multi‑Line Comment (/* ... */) Used for longer explanations or temporarily disabling blocks of code.
     /*
     This is a multi-line comment.
     It can span multiple lines.
     Useful for documentation or debugging.
     */
   Inline Comments (End of Line)
      location = "East US"  # Azure region
2- Strings are represented by double quoted sequence,   Single quotes (' ') are not allowed
      name     = "my-resource-group"
3- Terraform (HCL) uses Heredoc syntax to represent multi‑line strings

Basic Heredoc Syntax
value = <<EOF
This is a
multi-line
string
EOF

Indented Heredoc (Preferred)
value = <<-EOF
  This is a
  multi-line
  string
EOF
4- Values are assigned as <key>=<value>
